18/06/2009
TIRANA, Albania -- The Central Election Commission (CEC) has asked broadcasters to give more air time to certain political parties that saw their campaign slots reduced, media reported Wednesday (June 17th).
At its meeting, the CEC focused mainly on distributing air time between the main political parties -- the ruling Democratic Party and the main opposition Socialist Party.
Albanians head to the polls on June 28th.
(News 24, Start, Top Channel, Balkan Web - 17/06/09)
